

"In 2004 Judith Donath provided a useful, long definition of "sociable media." She started: "'''Sociable media are media that enhance communication and the formation of social ties among people'''. Such media are not new – letter writing can be traced back thousands of years – but the advent of the computer has brought about an immense number of new forms."

'''The term *sociable* media acknowledges the possibility of sociality instead of blindly assuming that the online millions will simply come if you open up a room'''. "Sociable web media,"
then, specifies the meaning a bit more as it separates the meaning from its offline equivalents."
(Trebor Scholz, IDC mailing list, February 2007)

